\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. I. helvetica} Weber, {\i Pl. Min. Cogn. Dec.} 17 (1784) ({\i I. vaillantii} (All.) Vill.). Erect, grey-tomentose perennial up to 150 cm. Leaves entire to serrate-dentate, puberulent above, grey tomentose beneath, the lower 8-12 × 1·5-2·5 cm, lanceolate or elliptic-lanceolate, the upper sessile, cuneate at base. Capitula medium to large; involucre 10-13 mm, hemispherical; bracts tomentose, the outer 6-7 × 1·5-2 mm, ovate-lanceolate with recurved apex, the inner 8-10 × 0·7-1 mm, linear. Ligules 15-20 mm, much exceeding the involucre. Achenes 2-2·5 mm, glabrous or sparsely hairy at apex; pappus with c. 30 setae.{\i  Woods and stream-sides.  • From E. Spain to S.W. Germany and N.W. Italy.} Ga Ge He Hs It.
