\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. I. germanica} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 883 (1753). Erect, somewhat tomentose perennial 30-60 cm. Leaves denticulate, sparsely hairy above, moderately densely hairy beneath, the lower 4·5-10 × 1-3 cm, oblong to ovate, the upper sessile, cordate, amplexicaul. Capitula 7-11 mm in diameter; involucre 7-10 mm, cylindrical; bracts tomentose, the outer c. 3 × 2 mm, ovate with recurved apex, the inner 5-8 × 0·5-0·7 mm, linear. Ligules 8-11 mm, not or only slightly exceeding the involucre. Achenes c. 1·5 mm, glabrous; pappus with c. 30 setae. 2n = 16.{\i  C. & S.E. Europe, extending northwards to} c. 54° {\i N. in C. Russia.} Al Au Bu Cz Ge Gr Hu Ju Po Rm Rs (C, W, K, E) Tu.
